<!--
  PIGLET (Path Integral Generalized Langevin Equation Thermostat) configuration.
  Uses a colored-noise GLE thermostat to achieve quantum convergence with
  significantly fewer beads than standard PILE.

  Key advantage: P=32 with PIGLET achieves accuracy comparable to P=128
  with standard thermostats, reducing computational cost by ~4x.

  The A matrix (6x6) encodes the optimized GLE parameters fitted to
  match the quantum harmonic oscillator free energy.

  Reference: Ceriotti and Manolopoulos, Phys. Rev. Lett. 109, 100604 (2012)
-->
